HEADWORD: Praline
<hw>Pra"line</hw> <pr>(pr⟦aum⟧"l⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A confection made of nut kernels, usually of
almonds, roasted in boiling sugar until brown and crisp.</def></p>

<p><q>Bonbons, <qex>pralines</qex>, . . . saccharine, crystalline
substances of all kinds and colors.</q> <rj><qau>Du
Maurier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

